\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. cylindrica} (Willd.) W. Greuter,{\i  Boissiera}{\b  13}: 177 (1967) ({\i Monerma cylindrica} (Willd.) Cosson & Durieu,{\i  Lepturus cylindricus} (Willd.) Trin.). Stems 5-35 cm, erect or ascending, smooth and glabrous. Leaves up to c. 7 cm × 2·5 mm, scabrid above; ligule up to c. 0·5 mm, truncate, denticulate; uppermost sheath distinctly inflated. Spike up to 25 cm, straight or somewhat curved, rigid. Spikelets 5-8 mm, somewhat longer than the internodes. Glumes ovate-lanceolate, acuminate. Anthers 2·5-3·5 mm. Chasmogamous. 2n = 26.{\i  Saline or gypsaceous soils. S. Europe.} Al Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Rs (K) Sa Si Tu.
