\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Leaves linear; silica-bodies oblong; 2-celled micro-hairs absent; ligule membranous. Inflorescence a panicle, usually dense and cylindrical to ovoid. Spikelets strongly compressed laterally, with usually 3 florets, the lower 2 reduced to the small lemma or 1 or both absent. Rhachilla disarticulating above the glumes but not between the florets. Sometimes spikelets in groups of 5-7, one fertile and sessile, the remainder sterile and pedicellate, the group falling entire. Glumes longer than the florets. Fertile lemma indurate at maturity, unawned. Lodicules 2. Stamens 3. Ovary glabrous; styles 2. Grain with short, oblong hilum; starch-grains compound. Chromosomes large; basic number 5, 6, 7.
